  "faq": [
    {
      "question": {
        "en-US": "Which phrases are most useful on a first Italy trip?",
        "zh-CN": "第一次去意大利旅行，最值得先准备哪几组短语？"
      },
      "answer": {
        "en-US": "Start with transport, dining, and hotel. That covers trains, check-in, coffee bars, and restaurant basics, which usually make up the first full day in Italy.",
        "zh-CN": "建议先看交通、餐饮和酒店，这三组基本能覆盖火车、入住、咖啡吧和餐厅基础沟通，通常就是在意大利第一整天最常用到的内容。"
      }
    },
    {
      "question": {
        "en-US": "Why are dining phrases especially important in Italy?",
        "zh-CN": "为什么在意大利旅行时，餐饮短语特别重要？"
      },
      "answer": {
        "en-US": "They help with reservation timing, allergies, coperto questions, takeaway requests, and asking for the bill. Those are common details in Italy and easy to mis-handle without a phrase ready.",
        "zh-CN": "因为它们能帮你处理预订时间、过敏说明、coperto、打包外带和要账单这些高频细节；这些场景在意大利很常见，没有现成短语时很容易沟通不清。"
      }
    }
  ]
